This paper focuses on learning a robot controller for contact-rich manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep reinforcement learning and self-supervision also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of visual feedback, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the use of self-supervision for representation learning suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluation of the method on a physical robot suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
